cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB

The paper deals with content-based searching and information extraction from large text collections, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses language detection and extraction, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The use of visualization techniques for efficient exploration of data can be categorized under Cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also deals with the analysis of confidential data, which can be categorized under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of open-source software, which can be categorized under Databases (cs.DB).
